.TH SysSolarisInfo 3 "Last change: 9 March 2004" "Release 0.5" "Ulm's Oberon System"
.SH NAME
SysSolarisInfo \- extract platform information under Solaris
.SH SYNOPSIS
.Pg
PROCEDURE GetArchitecture(VAR name: ARRAY OF CHAR);
PROCEDURE GetIsAList(VAR name: ARRAY OF CHAR);
PROCEDURE GetPlatform(VAR name: ARRAY OF CHAR);
PROCEDURE GetHardwareProvider(VAR name: ARRAY OF CHAR);
PROCEDURE GetHardwareSerial(VAR name: ARRAY OF CHAR);
.Pe
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I SysSolarisInfo
extracts various platform informations using the \fIsysinfo(2)\fP
system call under Solaris.
.PP
.I GetArchitecture
returns the basic instruction set architecture, e.g. ``sparc''
or ``i386''.
.PP
.I GetIsAList
returns a space-separated list of instruction set variants that
are supported by the current system, e.g. ``sparcv9''.
See \fIisalist(5)\fP for a detailed list.
.PP
.I GetPlatform
returns the name of the hardware platform, e.g. ``SUNW,Sun-Fire-V240''.
.PP
.I GetHardwareProvider
returns the name of the hardware manufacturer.
.PP
.I GetHardwareSerial
returns the ASCII representation of the hardware serial number.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.Tb SPARCSolarisArchitecture(3)
.Tp Architectures(3)
general classification of hardware architectures and operating systems
.Tp SPARCSolarisArchitecture(3)
extracts the platform information on SPARC/Solaris platforms
using this module and makes it available through \fIArchitectures(3)\fP
.Te
